chippie
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:usu. pl., a thin slice of potato fried until crisp and eaten cold; a potato crisp; from (potato) chip US = (potato) crisp, possibly the early form used in NZ:
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:chip
